ull}, {"name": "flags", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Receive a Python object as a message using pickle to serialize.\n\n# Parameters\n\nflags\n\n: Any valid flags for {func}`Socket.recv`.\n\n# Returns\n\nobj\n\n: The Python object that arrives as a message.\n\n# Raises\n\nZMQError\n\n: for any of the reasons {func}`~Socket.recv` might fail\n"]}, {"name": "zmq_anyio._socket.Socket.arecv_serialized", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "deserialize", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "flags", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "copy", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Receive a message with a custom deserialization function.\n\n:::{versionadded} 17\n:::\n\n# Parameters\n\ndeserialize\n\n: The deserialization function to use.\n  deserialize will be called with one argument: the list of frames\n  returned by recv_multipart() and can return any object.\n\nflags\n\n: Any valid flags for {func}`Socket.recv`.\n\ncopy\n\n: Whether to recv bytes or Frame objects.\n\n# Returns\n\nobj\n\n: The object returned by the deserialization function.\n\n# Raises\n\nZMQError\n\n: for any of the reasons {func}`~Socket.recv` might fail\n"]}, {"name": "zmq_anyio._socket.Socket.arecv_multipart", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "flags", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "copy", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "track", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}],