ickle.DEFAULT_PROTOCOL\n  where defined, and pickle.HIGHEST_PROTOCOL elsewhere.\n"]}, {"name": "zmq_anyio._socket.Socket.asend_serialized", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "serialize", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "flags", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "copy", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Send a message with a custom serialization function.\n\n:::{versionadded} 17\n:::\n\n# Parameters\n\nmsg : The message to be sent. Can be any object serializable by `serialize`.\nserialize : callable\n\n> The serialization function to use.\n> serialize(msg) should return an iterable of sendable message frames\n> (e.g. bytes objects), which will be passed to send_multipart.\n\nflags\n\n: Any valid flags for {func}`Socket.send`.\n\ncopy\n\n: Whether to copy the frames.\n"]}, {"name": "zmq_anyio._socket.Socket.asend_multipart", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg_parts", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "flags", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "copy", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "track", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "zmq.MessageTracker | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zmq_anyio._socket.Socket._deserialize", "asynchronous": fa